                            <comment id="104063" author="snicoll" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2014 08:56:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, the cache level works as advertized and can be overridden even when a transaction manager is present. That being said, as a general rule, it is best to fetch a fresh connection and session. Some JavaEE server may accept that extra tuning though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also clarified the role of &lt;tt&gt;sessionTransacted&lt;/tt&gt; that can be seen as a (almost) full replacement of what used to be done by &lt;tt&gt;JmsTransactionManager&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
